          "assignees": [],
          "author_association": "MEMBER",
          "body": "Decide whether to flip the reorganize-level default for `Page.reorganize_page(sidenote_max_height_ratio=...)` from `None` (legacy x-only) to e.g. `0.85` (more aggressive, bbox-height-aware).\n\nBbox-height pass already shipped; `detect_geometric_sidenotes(max_height_ratio=...)` rejects a margin cluster unless its median bbox height is `<= ratio * body_median_height`. Default `None` preserves legacy behaviour. Flipping the default needs evidence that `0.85`-style gating helps the corpus more than it hurts on real fixtures.\n\nThis is a tuning slice, not a coding slice: do a fixture sweep (and likely add fixtures) before changing the default.\n\nSource: docs/ROADMAP.md (Glyph-size analysis - Default-flip decision).\nSpec: docs/specs/03-reorganize-pipeline.md\n\n## Acceptance\n- [ ] Sweep all `tests/fixtures/layout_regression/` fixtures with `0.85` and record diffs vs `None`\n- [ ] Add at least one fixture that demonstrates the gating helps (tall sidenote currently misclassified as body)\n- [ ] Decision recorded in spec/ROADMAP: keep `None` default, or flip to `0.85`\n- [ ] If default is flipped, all existing fixtures still pass or have reviewed/accepted diffs\n",
          "closed_at": null,
